race.comment: INQUISITOR (5) was quickly back on track beaten a nose at Toowoomba in stronger. Needs a good Looker ride from the wide gate, but the extra metres suit and he's well placed. ALABAMA GIRL (10) draws even wider but there was a lot to like about her CL1 win here 16 days ago. Has a key gear switch and Jett Newman stays aboard. GAMING (6) was good here first-up but didn't manage the spike to this distance at Lismore. He will be better for that and has claims with average luck from a sticky barrier. OLIVERSHARE (11) can show more third-up and will be around the mark. SPILLS (3) drew out and pushed forward early but weakened out of it late when eighth over 1400m at this track last time. Has a low draw this time and can bounce back.
